The paper proposes a deep learning approach for co-saliency detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The approach also involves learning a semantics-aware image representation and collaborative learning, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of convolutional neural networks and end-to-end learning also suggests the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
